{
  "stem": "11882.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But for him, they were-- even if they baptized themselves back 150 years ago-- they were Jewish race, as he called it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "He called it race.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And should be-- we all know what he had in mind.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But it didn't penetrate very quickly that he meant Hitler business, you know?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, there had been anti-SemitIsm in the world.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "People knew.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was anti-Irish in Boston, there was a anti-Italian wherever there are a large-- a lot of it in America-- immigrant Italians.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nobody knew that Hitler meant what he was saying.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A few people believed him, and it registered right away what Hitler amounted to, and what he would do for the poor Jewish people, for for the Germans, too, for the Europeans, for the-- it changed my life-- for the Americans.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They didn't know what he would do.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But there is a man, Robert Kempner, who knew-- even as Hitler arrived, and before he arrived, in the 1920s, when he was rampaging around Germany, getting the riff-Raff of Germany together to follow him in the streets-- and Germany had many problems, it is true.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Economic problems, unemployment, and people with little to do following Hitler in the streets, as they say, like the pied piper of Hamelin and loving Hitler and swearing by Hitler.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this man, Robert Kempner, born a few weeks before the end of the century, in October before the new century-- not our coming new century, but the 1900 beginning-- realized in very early life-- he was very active politically and mentally and already a journalist in his 20s and a lawyer, and went into government work.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he realized, that man is poison for everyone here.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I arrived in October, 1937.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was under treatment by a medical doctor.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
